<p>West Virginia's solar resource compares favorably to states like Pennsylvania and Ohio, and technological advances in panel efficiency have made solar viable even in areas with moderate solar irradiance. Modern panels can generate electricity even on cloudy days, and West Virginia's relatively cool temperatures actually improve panel efficiency compared to hotter climates where panels can overheat and lose productivity.</p>

